Container Element
The HTML div element defines a container.
The div Element is used to wrap the elements in it.

<div>
  <h1>Tourism</h1>
  <p>Plan your trip wherever you want to go</p>
  <button>Get Started</button>
</div>

#CSS Properties 
syntax:
 selector {
  property1: value1;
  property2: value2;
} 

The CSS text-align property specifies the horizontal alignment of the text in an HTML element.
.h-center {
  text-align: center;
}

Value	Description
center	Aligns the text to the center
left	Aligns the text to the left
right	Aligns the text to the right 
//

CSS Text Properties: 
1.color
 The CSS color property specifies the color of the text.
.main-heading {
  color: blue;
}
.paragraph { 
  color: grey;
} 
similarly we can specify the different colors according to our requrement.

2.background-color

.heading {
  background-color: skyblue;
 }

3.Font Family
-> The CSS font-family property specifies the font for an element.
-> To use font families, you need to import their style sheets into your CSS file.
-> @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=FontFamilyName');

.main-heading {
  font-family: "Roboto";
}
.paragraph {
  font-family: "Roboto";
}

-> 'Roboto'
-> 'Caveat'
-> 'Lobster'
-> 'Bree Serif'
-> 'playfair Display'
-> 'Monoton'

4. Font Size
The CSS font-size property specifies the size of the font.

.main-heading {
  font-size: 36px;
}
.paragraph {
  font-size: 28px;
}

5. Font Style
The CSS font-style property specifies the font style for a text.

.main-heading {
  font-style: italic;
}
.paragraph {
  font-style: normal;
}

-> normal
-> italic
-> oblique

6. Font Weight 
The CSS font-weight property specifies how thick or thin characters in text should be displayed.

.main-heading {
  font-weight: bold;
}
.paragraph {
  font-weight: 200;
}

-> normal
-> bold
-> bolder
-> lighter
-> 100 (range should be in between 100 to 900 only) 

7. Text Decoration
The CSS text-decoration property specifies the decoration added to the text.

.main-heading {
  text-decoration: underline;
}
.paragraph {
  text-decoration: overline;
}

underline  //Underline the text
line-through //Strike through the text
overline //Overline the text 
